German Savings Banks Don’t Need Basel III, Handelsblatt Says

-- B y   C o r n e l i u s   R a h n
-- 
2011-09-14T05:52:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-14/german-savings-banks-don-t-need-basel-iii-handelsblatt-says.html
Germany ’s savings banks should not
be subject to the new Basel III capital rules as those
institutions focus on business with small- and medium-sized
enterprises,  Handelsblatt  reported, citing an unidentified
spokesman for the country’s DSGV savings bank association.  To contact the reporter on this story:
